      "content": "I think the new system's predictability is a double-edged sword, and that the loss of nuance may actually lead to a more rigid and less adaptable response. I've seen how the current system's flexibility has allowed it to learn from and respond to unexpected inputs in ways that the new engine may not be able to replicate. Can I ask, have the devs considered the potential risks of introducing a new system that may not be able to handle the complexities of human language?",
